# Week 8 JSON Notes

## What JSON Means
JSON stands for JavaScript Object Notation. In this assignment, I am using it as a readable way to save app information in a file.

## What My App Needs To Remember
- Project name: MelodyOrganizer
- Team member names: Alexa Lopez (Individual Project)
- Folder names: Previous Playlist
- File names: RateSong
- Last saved location: Main Playlist
- Other information: N/A

## Variables Connected To JSON
- Variable name: SongName
- Data type: string
- What it stores: the name of a song. this can be either used in the song recommendations,
Favorite Tracks, or Song Review file
- Why the app needs it: the app needs to be able to store the users previous 
ratings/tracks/reviews so tehy can either look back to their favorite songs, refresh their memory, etc.

## Save Process
1. The user enters information.
2. The app stores that information in variables or objects.
3. The app converts the information into JSON.
4. The app writes the JSON to a file.

